    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Noon (12:05:00) in the Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes - Aric stands among the towering bookshelves, the mysterious Hexaphrenicon open in his hands. The blank pages seem to drink in the light, and those strange shadows continue their eternal dance beneath the surface. The six-pupiled eye symbol on the cover watches you like a patient predator.\n\nThe elderly librarian remains standing now, watching you with an expression caught between curiosity and concern. His earlier cryptic warning hangs in the air: \"The most dangerous books often contain the most valuable knowledge.\"\n\nThe book seems to pulse with dormant power, waiting for someone brave\u2014or foolish\u2014enough to unlock its secrets.",
